# Workspace: `excalidraw-app`

## Role

- **Full product shell**: Vite React app that embeds `@excalidraw/excalidraw`, adds hosting-specific features (collaboration, persistence, PWA, analytics, Firebase, Sentry, etc.).
- **Not published as `@excalidraw/excalidraw`** — this is private app code; library behavior belongs in `packages/excalidraw`.

## Boundaries

- Import the editor via **`@excalidraw/excalidraw`** (and other `@excalidraw/*` packages). Avoid deep-importing private internals of the library unless already established in this app — prefer public exports.
- **`vite.config.mts`** aliases point at `packages/*` source — keep alias targets consistent with monorepo layout when adding new workspace paths.

## Conventions

- App wiring (routing, collab socket URLs, env-based config) lives here; **core editor rules** (actions, scene invariants) still belong in `packages/excalidraw` or `packages/element`.
- Respect **secrets via env** (Firebase, Sentry DSN, collab endpoints) — never commit tokens (see `security.mdc`).
- Dev entry: `yarn start` from repo root (runs app dev server). Build: `yarn build` (app production build). Tests: `excalidraw-app/tests/` with Vitest.

## How to verify

- `yarn build` from repo root (Vite production build for `excalidraw-app`).
- `yarn test:app --watch=false` (includes `excalidraw-app/tests/` via root Vitest config).
- For collab/Firebase/env changes: `yarn start` and exercise the affected flow manually; confirm secrets stay in env, not in source.
- Broader gate when unsure: `yarn test:all`.
